==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Osteoporosis
<hw>Os`te*o*po*ro"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.;
<ets>osteo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>po`ros</grk> pore.]</ety> <fld>(Med. &
Physiol.)</fld> <def>An absorption of bone so that the bone tissue
becomes unusually porous. It occurs especially in elderly men and
postmenopausal women, and predisposes the elderly to fractures of the
bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osteopterygious</ent>⟦br⟧
